When using a file as a struct, how do I refer to that struct from inside that file?
In Zig, when you define a struct within a file, you can refer to that struct using the file's name as a namespace. However, if you want to refer to the struct from within the same file, you can use `@This()` to get a reference to the current file's namespace.

Here's how you can modify your code to use `@This()` to refer to the `Cell` struct from within the same file:

```zig
const rl = @import("raylib");

const Direction = @import("./direction.zig").Direction;

pub const Cell = struct {
    x: i32,
    y: i32,

    pub fn init(x: i32, y: i32) Cell {
        return Cell{ .x = x, .y = y };
    }

    pub fn vector2(self: Cell) rl.Vector2 {
        return rl.Vector2{
            @floatFromInt(self.x),
            @floatFromInt(self.y),
        };
    }

    pub fn renderAt(self: Cell) void {
        self.renderAtFacing(.Right);
    }

    pub fn renderAtFacing(self: Cell, dir: Direction) void {
        const pos = self.vector2();
        rl.gl.rlTranslatef(pos.x, pos.y, 0);
        rl.gl.rlRotatef(dir.degrees(), 0, 0, 1);
    }
};

// Example usage within the same file
pub fn exampleUsage() void {
    const cell = Cell.init(10, 20);
    cell.renderAt();
}
```

In this example, the `Cell` struct is defined within the file, and you can refer to it directly using `Cell` within the same file. The `exampleUsage` function demonstrates how you can create an instance of `Cell` and call its methods.
